This paper presents a new architecture for machine learning that involves learning models based on formal mathematical representations of the domain of interest and exposing latent variables. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of traditional prediction or classification mechanisms, which are common in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing, which falls under the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of image recognition, which falls under the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of low shot and zero shot training, which is relevant to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SD).
